1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,600
Here's what science actually says about antiviral vs antibiotic.

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:06,800
Many confuse them, but they serve different purposes.

3
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:09,600
Antivirals target viruses, while antibiotics fight bacteria.

4
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:10,400
Simple, right?

5
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:11,600
Not so fast.

6
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:14,000
Imagine battling the flu with antibiotics!

7
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,200
It won’t work.

8
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:16,000
But why?

9
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:18,800
Because they’re designed for entirely different enemies.

10
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:25,600
Research indicates that using antibiotics against viruses can lead to resistance, making bacterial infections harder to treat.

11
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:29,600
So next time you’re sick, remember: choose the right treatment.

12
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:32,400
Ask your doctor for the best advice.

13
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:34,400
Curious for more science tips?

14
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:36,800
Like and follow for more insights!
